510
00:24:29.675 --> 00:24:32.495
and real world experiences help students reach their

511
00:24:32.525 --> 00:24:33.575
full potential.

512
00:24:34.445 --> 00:24:35.695
They engage families

513
00:24:36.195 --> 00:24:39.775
and communities, partnering with residents to identify

514
00:24:39.875 --> 00:24:41.175
and meet community needs.

515
00:24:41.785 --> 00:24:45.295
Makes everyone feel safe, welcome and involved in school.

516
00:24:46.245 --> 00:24:50.095
They lead in collaboration, inclusive decision making,

517
00:24:50.195 --> 00:24:53.895
and peer learning builds trust among students, educators,

518
00:24:54.615 --> 00:24:55.775
families, and communities.

519
00:24:56.485 --> 00:24:59.255
When a school stands on these four pillars,

520
00:25:00.005 --> 00:25:01.295
it's a community school

521
00:25:02.375 --> 00:25:04.775
research supports this four pillar approach,

522
00:25:05.355 --> 00:25:07.695
but there's no one size fits all model.

523
00:25:08.105 --> 00:25:10.015
Every community school is different

524
00:25:10.015 --> 00:25:12.175
because each community is different.

525
00:25:13.055 --> 00:25:15.695
Figuring out what it looks like in your community starts

526
